# How to use alembic

Alembic is a database migrations tool written by the author of SQLAlchemy.

See: https://alembic.sqlalchemy.org/en/latest/tutorial.html

```bash
# Check current revision
docker compose exec backend alembic history --indicate-current

# Create a new revision
docker compose exec backend alembic revision --autogenerate -m "<upgrade-message-here>"

# Upgrade to the most recent version. You can use a specific hash too
docker compose exec backend alembic upgrade heads

# Downgrade to a specific version
docker compose exec backend alembic downgrade <hash> 
```
